<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Cypriot authorities deserve to be commended for their dedication
and efficiency in swiftly handling the event from its operative
aspects and in safeguarding adequate compensations to the affected
animal owners.

The decision to apply stamping out in the flocks found "infected" on
ground of several positive serological tests in adult animals --
while virus/antigen remaining undetected -- is assumed to be the
outcome of EU policy. Additional commentary, in particular explaining
the decision -- or correcting the said assumption -- will be welcomed.

The commentary to the previous posting in this thread, 20071114.3698,
included the following: "The positive 3ABC tests, detecting Non
Specific Proteins (NSP), may be indicative of a past application of
(partly or poorly purified) inactivated FMD vaccines." 'Non Specific
Proteins' should have read 'Non Structural Proteins'. We are grateful
to Dr Hagai Yadin for drawing out attention to the lapse. - Mod.AS]
